# Keep the Docker build context lean and the `COPY . .` layer cacheable.
#
# Local Gradle runs regenerate build/, bin/ and .gradle/ on every invocation.
# If those are sent into the build context, the `COPY . .` layer hash changes
# every build, invalidating Docker's layer cache and forcing a full rebuild —
# which is what caused the build cache to balloon and fill the disk. Excluding
# them keeps builds fast and cache reuse high. The multi-stage Dockerfile
# rebuilds the jar inside the `gradle` image, so these are never needed.

# Gradle build outputs / caches
build/
bin/
.gradle/

# IDE / editor / OS noise
.idea/
*.iml
.vscode/
.DS_Store

# VCS
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Docs (not needed to build the jar)
HELP.md
*.md

# TLS keystores / certs must never enter the image via the build context;
# the Dockerfile generates them at build time.
certs/
*.p12
*.jks
*.pem
*.key
